<HEADLINE>
FT  21 JAN 94 / Possible relations
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By NIKKI TAIT
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   SYDNEY
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Australian government officials yesterday admitted they had been approached
by North Korea, over the possibility of restoring diplomatic relations,
severed unilaterally by the North Koreans almost two decades ago, Nikki Tait
reports from Sydney. But Mr Gordon Bilney, acting minister for foreign
affairs, said the talks were 'very informal and very tentative discussions.
. . essentially diplomatic-level consultations'. 'There haven't been
political contacts of any kind - it's not time for those,' he said.
