<HEADLINE>
FT  21 JAN 94 / World News in Brief: Winston Silcott appeal refused
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Home secretary Michael Howard decided not to refer the case of Winston
Silcott, serving life for the murder of boxer Anthony Smith in 1984, back to
the Court of Appeal. Silcott's conviction for the murder of Pc Keith
Blakelock in the 1985 Broadwater Farm riots in Tottenham, north London, was
quashed in 1991.
