FT  20 JAN 94 / International Company News: Gyllenhammer to step down as
vice-chairman of SE-Banken
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By CHRISTOPHER BROWN-HUMES
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   STOCKHOLM
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Mr Pehr Gyllenhammar is stepping down as a vice-chairman of Skandinaviska
Enskilda Banken.
'It is natural that after leaving Volvo, I should also leave the SE-Banken
board so that I remain free for the future,' he said.
Mr Gyllenhammar has been a board member at SE-Banken since 1979, and
vice-chairman since 1991. He is expected to step down at the bank's annual
general meeting in April.
