FT  20 JAN 94 / International Company News: Ipsco to build Dollars 400m
steel mill in Iowa
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ROBERT GIBBENS
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   MONTREAL
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Ipsco, western Canada's leading steelmaker, has chosen south-eastern Iowa
for a USDollars 400m mini-mill to produce hot-rolled coil and plate.
The mill, with 1m tonnes annual capacity, will be built under a turnkey
contract by Germany's Mannesmann Demag. It will double Ipsco's steelmaking
capacity.
It will make coil up to 96 inches wide and  3/4 inch thick and plate up to
120 inches wide and two inches thick. The workforce will total 300 people
and will start production in 1996.
Mr Roger Phillips, president, said Ipsco chose Iowa because of an abundant
supply of scrap, low taxes and state aid.
