FT  20 JAN 94 / UK Company News: Massey Ferguson in Japanese link
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Massey Ferguson, the US-owned farm equipment group, and Iseki of Japan have
agreed to co-operate in the UK and Irish markets for turf and grass
equipment.
MF's grass equipment division has been appointed exclusive distributor for
Iseki products from February 1. Iseki is one of the world's biggest
manufacturers of compact tractors.
The move has been prompted by the largely complementary nature of the two
companies' grass machinery ranges, and builds on existing co-operation
between them elsewhere.
