FT  20 JAN 94 / People: Serif
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Eric Holroyd, 67, has stepped down as chief executive of Serif, less than a
month after the refinancing of the loss-making printing and packaging group.
John Sandiford, the company's finance director, said that Holroyd was a
company doctor and now that the refinancing had been completed there was
less need for his services.
Holroyd will remain on the board as a non-executive director and a new chief
executive is being sought.
