<HEADLINE>
FT  20 JAN 94 / Venables keeps control of club
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Terry Venables retained control of his social club Scribes West yesterday
when a deal to save the business from insolvency proceedings was finalised
in the high court.
By agreement the court dismissed a winding-up petition based on a debt of
pounds 150,000 claimed by Mr Vincent Isaacs, chairman of insurance group
general portfolio, who was a backer of the original Scribes Club near Fleet
Street.
At a two-minute hearing Mr Justice Knox was told a sum of money -
undisclosed but believed to be about pounds 50,000 - had been paid 'in full
and final satisfaction' of the petitioner's claim against Scribes West in
Kensington, West London.
The petition was supported by customs and excise, claiming a vat debt, but
it did not apply to be substituted as petitioner or take any part in the
proceedings. No order for costs was sought against the club company.
</TEXT>
