<HEADLINE>
FT  20 JAN 94 / Renault to help after accidents
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Renault UK is launching a fresh weapon in the UK new car sales war -
accident management on each car sold.
It has formed a venture with Accident Management Company, part of a
northern-based fleet management group, to take over administration of the
entire aftermath of an accident, from contact with insurers to overseeing
repairs, at no cost to the motorist.
The scheme, available for fleet and private buyers, already covers 31,000
Renault vehicles in the UK and is expected to be extended to more than
130,000 by the end of this year.
