<TEXT>
Bitter Arctic weather closed factories, businesses and government offices
across the US midwest and Atlantic seaboard yesterday, with the disruption
expected to continue today, writes Martin Dickson in New York.
In Washington DC all non-essential federal employees were sent home at 3pm
