<TEXT>
CBS may have lost its broadcasting rights for American football, but it has
has reasserted its claims as a top sports television network by winning the
US television rights for the 1998 winter Olympics.
The network was due to announce yesterday it had secured the rights for the
winter games, to be held in Nagano, Japan, with a record bid of Dollars 375m
(Pounds 253.3m). CBS televised the Albertville games in 1992 and will also
